39class SendStatisticsProxy : public VideoStreamEncoderObserver,
40 public ReportBlockDataObserver,
41 public RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver,
42 public StreamDataCountersCallback,
43 public BitrateStatisticsObserver,
44 public FrameCountObserver,
45 public SendSideDelayObserver {
46 public:
47 static const int kStatsTimeoutMs;
48 // Number of required samples to be collected before a metric is added
49 // to a rtc histogram.
50 static const int kMinRequiredMetricsSamples = 200;
51
52 SendStatisticsProxy(Clock* clock,
53 const VideoSendStream::Config& config,
54 VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType content_type);
55 ~SendStatisticsProxy() override;
56
57 virtual VideoSendStream::Stats GetStats();
58
59 void OnSendEncodedImage(const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
60 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_info) override;
61
62 void OnEncoderImplementationChanged(
63 const std::string& implementation_name) override;
64
65 // Used to update incoming frame rate.

67
68 // Dropped frame stats.
69 void OnFrameDropped(DropReason) override;
70
71 // Adaptation stats.
72 void OnAdaptationChanged(
73 VideoAdaptationReason reason,
74 const VideoAdaptationCounters& cpu_counters,
75 const VideoAdaptationCounters& quality_counters) override;
76 void ClearAdaptationStats() override;
77 void UpdateAdaptationSettings(AdaptationSettings cpu_settings,
78 AdaptationSettings quality_settings) override;
79
80 void OnBitrateAllocationUpdated(
81 const VideoCodec& codec,
82 const VideoBitrateAllocation& allocation) override;
83
84 void OnEncoderInternalScalerUpdate(bool is_scaled) override;
85
86 void OnMinPixelLimitReached() override;
87 void OnInitialQualityResolutionAdaptDown() override;
88
89 void OnSuspendChange(bool is_suspended) override;
90 void OnInactiveSsrc(uint32_t ssrc);
91
92 // Used to indicate change in content type, which may require a change in
93 // how stats are collected.
94 void OnEncoderReconfigured(const VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config,
95 const std::vector<VideoStream>& streams) override;

97 // Used to update the encoder target rate.

99
100 // Implements CpuOveruseMetricsObserver.
101 void OnEncodedFrameTimeMeasured(int encode_time_ms,
102 int encode_usage_percent) override;
103
104 int GetInputFrameRate() const override;
105 int GetSendFrameRate() const;
106
107 protected:
108 // From ReportBlockDataObserver.
109 void OnReportBlockDataUpdated(ReportBlockData report_block_data) override;
110 // From RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver.
111 void RtcpPacketTypesCounterUpdated(
112 uint32_t ssrc,
113 const RtcpPacketTypeCounter& packet_counter) override;
114 // From StreamDataCountersCallback.
115 void DataCountersUpdated(const StreamDataCounters& counters,
116 uint32_t ssrc) override;
117
118 // From BitrateStatisticsObserver.
119 void Notify(uint32_t total_bitrate_bps,
120 uint32_t retransmit_bitrate_bps,
121 uint32_t ssrc) override;
122
123 // From FrameCountObserver.
124 void FrameCountUpdated(const FrameCounts& frame_counts,
125 uint32_t ssrc) override;
126
127 void SendSideDelayUpdated(int avg_delay_ms,
128 int max_delay_ms,
129 uint64_t total_delay_ms,
130 uint32_t ssrc) override;

132 private:
133 class SampleCounter {
134 public:
135 SampleCounter() : sum(0), num_samples(0) {}
136 ~SampleCounter() {}
137 void Add(int sample);
138 int Avg(int64_t min_required_samples) const;
139
140 private:
141 int64_t sum;
142 int64_t num_samples;
143 };
144 class BoolSampleCounter {
145 public:
146 BoolSampleCounter() : sum(0), num_samples(0) {}
147 ~BoolSampleCounter() {}
148 void Add(bool sample);
149 void Add(bool sample, int64_t count);
150 int Percent(int64_t min_required_samples) const;
151 int Permille(int64_t min_required_samples) const;
152
153 private:
154 int Fraction(int64_t min_required_samples, float multiplier) const;
155 int64_t sum;
156 int64_t num_samples;
157 };
158 struct StatsUpdateTimes {
159 StatsUpdateTimes() : resolution_update_ms(0), bitrate_update_ms(0) {}
160 int64_t resolution_update_ms;
161 int64_t bitrate_update_ms;
162 };
163 struct TargetRateUpdates {
164 TargetRateUpdates()
165 : pause_resume_events(0), last_paused_or_resumed(false), last_ms(-1) {}
166 int pause_resume_events;
167 bool last_paused_or_resumed;
168 int64_t last_ms;
169 };
170 struct FallbackEncoderInfo {
171 FallbackEncoderInfo();
172 bool is_possible = true;
173 bool is_active = false;
174 int on_off_events = 0;
175 int64_t elapsed_ms = 0;
176 absl::optional<int64_t> last_update_ms;
177 const int max_frame_diff_ms = 2000;
178 };
179 struct FallbackEncoderInfoDisabled {
180 bool is_possible = true;
181 bool min_pixel_limit_reached = false;
182 };
183 struct StatsTimer {
184 void Start(int64_t now_ms);
185 void Stop(int64_t now_ms);
186 void Restart(int64_t now_ms);
187 int64_t start_ms = -1;
188 int64_t total_ms = 0;
189 };
190 struct QpCounters {
191 SampleCounter vp8; // QP range: 0-127.
192 SampleCounter vp9; // QP range: 0-255.
193 SampleCounter h264; // QP range: 0-51.
194 };
195 struct AdaptChanges {
196 int down = 0;
197 int up = 0;
198 };
199
200 // Map holding encoded frames (mapped by timestamp).
201 // If simulcast layers are encoded on different threads, there is no guarantee
202 // that one frame of all layers are encoded before the next start.
203 struct TimestampOlderThan {
204 bool operator()(uint32_t ts1, uint32_t ts2) const {
205 return IsNewerTimestamp(ts2, ts1);
206 }
207 };
208 struct Frame {
209 Frame(int64_t send_ms, uint32_t width, uint32_t height, int simulcast_idx)
210 : send_ms(send_ms),
211 max_width(width),
212 max_height(height),
213 max_simulcast_idx(simulcast_idx) {}
214 const int64_t
215 send_ms; // Time when first frame with this timestamp is sent.
216 uint32_t max_width; // Max width with this timestamp.
217 uint32_t max_height; // Max height with this timestamp.
218 int max_simulcast_idx; // Max simulcast index with this timestamp.
219 };
220 typedef std::map<uint32_t, Frame, TimestampOlderThan> EncodedFrameMap;
221
222 void PurgeOldStats() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_);
223 VideoSendStream::StreamStats* GetStatsEntry(uint32_t ssrc)
224 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_);

243 AdaptationSettings quality_settings);
244
245 private:
246 VideoAdaptationCounters cpu_counts_;
247 AdaptationSettings cpu_settings_;
248 VideoAdaptationCounters quality_counts_;
249 AdaptationSettings quality_settings_;
250
251 MaskedAdaptationCounts Mask(const VideoAdaptationCounters& counters,
252 const AdaptationSettings& settings) const;
253 };

311 // Contains stats used for UMA histograms. These stats will be reset if
312 // content type changes between real-time video and screenshare, since these
313 // will be reported separately.
314 struct UmaSamplesContainer {
315 UmaSamplesContainer(const char* prefix,
316 const VideoSendStream::Stats& start_stats,
317 Clock* clock);
318 ~UmaSamplesContainer();
319
320 void UpdateHistograms(const RtpConfig& rtp_config,
321 const VideoSendStream::Stats& current_stats);
322
323 void InitializeBitrateCounters(const VideoSendStream::Stats& stats);
324
325 bool InsertEncodedFrame(const EncodedImage& encoded_frame,
326 int simulcast_idx);
327 void RemoveOld(int64_t now_ms);
328
329 const std::string uma_prefix_;
330 Clock* const clock_;
331 SampleCounter input_width_counter_;
332 SampleCounter input_height_counter_;
333 SampleCounter sent_width_counter_;
334 SampleCounter sent_height_counter_;
335 SampleCounter encode_time_counter_;
336 BoolSampleCounter key_frame_counter_;
337 BoolSampleCounter quality_limited_frame_counter_;
338 SampleCounter quality_downscales_counter_;
339 BoolSampleCounter cpu_limited_frame_counter_;
340 BoolSampleCounter bw_limited_frame_counter_;
341 SampleCounter bw_resolutions_disabled_counter_;
342 SampleCounter delay_counter_;
343 SampleCounter max_delay_counter_;
344 rtc::RateTracker input_frame_rate_tracker_;
345 RateCounter input_fps_counter_;
346 RateCounter sent_fps_counter_;
347 RateAccCounter total_byte_counter_;
348 RateAccCounter media_byte_counter_;
349 RateAccCounter rtx_byte_counter_;
350 RateAccCounter padding_byte_counter_;
351 RateAccCounter retransmit_byte_counter_;
352 RateAccCounter fec_byte_counter_;
353 int64_t first_rtcp_stats_time_ms_;
354 int64_t first_rtp_stats_time_ms_;
355 StatsTimer cpu_adapt_timer_;
356 StatsTimer quality_adapt_timer_;
357 BoolSampleCounter paused_time_counter_;
358 TargetRateUpdates target_rate_updates_;
359 BoolSampleCounter fallback_active_counter_;
360 FallbackEncoderInfo fallback_info_;
361 FallbackEncoderInfoDisabled fallback_info_disabled_;
362 ReportBlockStats report_block_stats_;
363 const VideoSendStream::Stats start_stats_;
364 size_t num_streams_; // Number of configured streams to encoder.
365 size_t num_pixels_highest_stream_;
366 EncodedFrameMap encoded_frames_;
367 AdaptChanges initial_quality_changes_;
368
369 std::map<int, QpCounters>
370 qp_counters_; // QP counters mapped by spatial idx.
371 };
372
373 std::unique_ptr<UmaSamplesContainer> uma_container_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_);
374};
